UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0378426684900104
AB  - In Australia, the task of developing a failure classification model for any one industrial sector is made difficult because of the small number of business failures from any one sector. This study develops a five variable business failure classification model for Australia which is sufficiently general to be applied across several industrial sectors. Instead of relying on traditional ratios, it uses an industry-relative approach in the classification model.
